# .gitattributes - fork protection for WinuX and its forks.
#
# WinuX is meant to be forked. Your fork keeps its own version of the files listed below while still
# pulling engine, module, and documentation improvements from upstream. The "ours" merge driver makes
# `git merge upstream/master` keep YOUR copy of each listed file and never overwrite it with WinuX's
# generic/example one.
#
# The driver is registered per clone by the bootstrap (it runs `git config merge.ours.driver true`).
# If you set up without the bootstrap, run that one command yourself, once. Git will not auto-register
# a merge driver from a cloned repo (a security boundary), so it is always a one-time local step.
#
# Personal CONFIG is handled differently and needs no attribute here: Configuration.psd1 stays the
# generic base and SHOULD track upstream; your personal values go in Configuration.local.psd1, which is
# deep-merged over the base at load. Upstream never tracks that file, so it never conflicts. (Commit it
# in your fork if you want it to sync across your machines.)
#
# NOTE for WinuX maintainers: these rules apply to this repo too, so a LOCAL merge of a PR that edits
# one of these files would keep the repo's version. Merge such PRs on GitHub, or reconcile by hand.

# Application install lists - each fork curates its own; WinuX ships a minimal example set.
Windows/PowerShell/Modules/Bootstrap/Data/WinGetApps.csv       merge=ours
Windows/PowerShell/Modules/Bootstrap/Data/ScoopApps.csv        merge=ours
Windows/PowerShell/Modules/Bootstrap/Data/ChocolateyApps.csv   merge=ours

# Personal payload configs - your real values; WinuX ships generic/blank templates.
Git/.gitconfig                                                 merge=ours
NuGet/nuget.config                                             merge=ours
Firefox/user.js                                                merge=ours

# Custom-area docs landing page - upstream ships a template; your fork lists its own custom
# pages there. (Custom code and per-module custom doc pages need no attribute: upstream never
# tracks those paths, so they can never conflict.)
docs/custom/README.md                                          merge=ours
